     <div type="to_the_reader">
   <pb facs="114"/>
   <head>A Postscript to the Readers.</head>
   <p>GEntle Readers, I am to satisfie you anent <gap reason="illegible" resp="#pdcc" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>vvo things you haue met vvithall in rea<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ding the foregoing Treatise, first, that the reasons and arguments novv and then are very concisely proposed, the syllogismes vvanting one of the premisses, or the conclusion, or both. And my reason of thus doing vvas, because I vvrote vnto men endued vvith Logick, at least, naturall, vvhich hauing the pith of the argument, is able enough to suggest inferences. The other thing is, that vvhereas there is sometimes cited <hi>Ke<gap reason="illegible" resp="#pdcc" extent="1 letter">
            <desc>•</desc>
         </gap>ker.</hi> System of Diuinitie, you vvould be pleased to haue recourse vnto that vvhich vvas printed at Geneua <hi>Ann. Dom. MDC. X<gap reason="illegible" resp="#pdcc" extent="1 letter">
            <desc>•</desc>
         </gap>.</hi> vvhere according to the order of pages, you shall find the points enlarged, vvhich are here but briefly touched.</p>
   <trailer>FINIS.</trailer>
   <pb facs="114"/>
</div>
